"The President of the Council also expressed, on behalf of the Government, his condolences for the victims of recent Russian attacks, > renewing the firm condemnation of these acts and underlining the urgency of an immediate and unconditional ceasefire, as well as the need for a concrete commitment by Moscow to initiate a peace process." This is what we read in a note of Palazzo Chigi issued after the meeting of leaders in the headquarters of the government.
"The President of the Council" Giorgia Meloni, during the interview with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky at Palazzo Chigi, "has welcomed the full availability of Ukraine for an immediate ceasefire. Now it is expected that Russia also demonstrates its willingness to pursue peace >" continues the note.&nbsp;
